_sText: dm_austere_facilityxx This is a minor re-make of dm_austere_facility. Change List: - Brightened Map Up - Railings Don't Block Bullets - Fixed Doors - Improved FPS Map Stats: - 64 Random Spawns - Cubemaps - Radar Map - Nav File The map is some kind of military-esque warehouse complex sorta thing. Most of the fighting takes place in the open warehouse and electrical area, but there is also a back hallway that runs along the back of the map. This map is good for open-area awping, but gives plenty of cover for players with other weapons to close in on their targets. If you have questions or comments, let me know!!

dm_austere_facility By: Natalya[AF] Map Features: - 48 Spawns - Cubemaps - Radar Map - Custom Textures This is the exact same as gg_austere_facility except for I've moved the spawns around so that it can be used for Death Match. There aren't any other differences. The textures are the skybox (look up in the main area to see stars) and a counter top in the tunnel area. It also has built in some skins for various props including the vending machines, van, pickup truck, and some other small stuff in the tunnels. The skins shouldn't show up on other maps and won't override any customs you have when you go to another map so don't worry about that happening. They will show up here only. Inspiration came from this map: gg_underground_z But all the work in my map is 100% mine and original. I didn't actually take anything out of underground z aside from ideas. Thanks to Seraphim for helping error test it. Anyway... I hope y'all enjoy the map.

A small and tight deathmatch map, themed in the Dust 2 style.

This is an incremented version of dm_dustbox.

Changes:
-------

* Optimized the map, added hints, fades, etc.
	- Made a lot of changes to what the game believes is visible from any one place, and hence what it draws
	- Map should now perform much more stably as the server population increases

* Add DD's on opposite sides of the map - Gives some nice additional gameplay

* Removed the dustclouds (performance)

* Extended / moved some walls inside (breaks centre up a bit, better performance)

* Changed the small breakaway doors to classic Dust door shape

* Added / moved several props, especially crates, to enable easier climbing

* Removed a member's name, added 2 other members' names

* Moved some names out of shadow

* Func-brushed name brushes, to make them non-solid

* Changed roof-dome props and moved palm-tree

* Raised sand-level near corner platform, to enable easy entry

* Added more cover on corner platform

The Story

Counter Terrorist
-----------------
CT found a group of terrorists in the act of adding weapons to their stockpile (obviously to do no good). The group is well known, and must be stopped. The mission is to take control of the compound, and sieze everything that isn't bolted down. They have been authorized to elliminate any resistance. 

Terrorist
----------
T are closing a deal with an illegal weapons supplier. The guns and ammo are needed desperately to support their many cells within the city. During the deal, a CT unit infiltrates the compound. The guns, ammo and money must be saved at all costs. 


P.S. Yes this map was based on a CoD4 map called Showdown.

Dm_amd_spider This map was created for ATi/AMD and their clan, Team ATi. The map is based on the internal workings of the motherboard, CPU, RAM and Graphics cards, and is based upon an ATi Spider platform rig. This means a rig consisting of only ATi/AMD certified parts. The parts in question here are the AMD Phenom Quad-Core CPU, the AMD 790FX Chipset (on the motherboard) and the ATi HD3870 Graphics card. In the map, you can travel quickly between each part, thanks to the HyperTransport 3.0 technology, which allows two packets of data (or players) to travel between each component at the same time. The data streams will boost you forward and through to the component it links to, which is designated by the sign posted next to the tunnel itself. There are 4 graphics cards, which are CrossfireX enabled, allowing quick access to each of the linked cards. Be careful of the fans though, they can suck you up and kill you if you get too close.
The majority of the map is quite open, with some small defenses, which encourage players to keep on their toes and use the defense as effectively as possible. The data tunnels add a twist, as you never know who might fly out at any time.
This map was created solely by Killo$ity, and was sent on to ATi before posting on the site. If credit is stolen, you will be dealt with severely.
Note to the community: Some of you may have heard me talking of a 'secret mapping project' a few months a go. I have been very protective about it, as I was made to sign an agreement, enforcing me not to leak any information until the map was complete, or ready for the public. This map, is that secret mapping project. It may not be what some people were expecting, but this is the outcome. Thank you all for understanding. I hope you all enjoy the map, thank you. Here's a short taster video of the map.
Enjoy!

Installation:

This is a simple death match map, constructed of 3 houses, their respectful gardens, and a front road connecting the 3. With numerous ways to travel around
the map, there's always a different route to take, and plenty of secrets to discover. Have fun, and rack up those frags!

Also, this map has some darker areas to contrast with the brighter ones, for a better experience, we suggest allowing flashlights to be used when playing, so that you can light up the darker areas if you wish. It all adds to the fun!

Objectives:

- Kill the enemies
- Dont overuse AWP
- and have fun! =)

- Bombsite is inaccessible, it exists only to ensure the round ends

This is the first map attempted by myself, Daev, and a lifelong friend of mine, Mike. We started messing around in Hammer a while back, and eventually decided to try to create something, in this case, based on our own houses. Being the simplistic two we are, we went with a Death Match map, seeing as there's also not enough room for a bomb site or hostage rescue. Some things aren't perfect yet, but it can make for one hell of a session with about 5vs5, but spawn points offers a max of 24vs24.
